# Graphics Principles

- Prioritize readability and deterministic visual communication over visual spectacle.
- Prefer geometry, palette, and shader-driven approaches over bespoke art asset dependency.
- Do not introduce effects that obscure item state, routing state, portal state, or topology state.
- If visual behavior changes gameplay comprehension, update graphics architecture and roadmap docs in the same task.
- For graphics-related implementation work, run `.cursor/skills/docs-implementation-gate/SKILL.md`.
- During graphics behavior changes, run `.cursor/skills/docs-change-policy-enforcer/SKILL.md` to enforce same-task documentation updates.
- If graphics guidance conflicts across docs, run `.cursor/skills/docs-source-truth-resolver/SKILL.md` before choosing implementation direction.
